rComments: Amazing prof! Anyone who doesn't like her is because they expected to put in no effort and get a good grade. Extremely helpful, knowledgable, personable, and caring. She is passionate about teaching and goes above and beyond to help her students. You will work hard but you will actually learn. Wish I had more than 350 characters, great prof!

Although I think we spent a little too much time with the book and didn't get enough to the nitty-gritty, the dirty grammar and things that actually help improve German, she showed a great interest and passion for the course and was very helpful in clarifying any questions we had.Very culturally knowledgable. And I'd totally do her.
She is not helpful at all.
I didn't like the course at all. The material she teaches is useless and will not help mankind in any way.

Well, the course moves very fast, but Marija is more like a friend than a professor and she treats her students on a personal basis. She takes the best qualities of a university professor and a high school teacher and merges them together. Plus she is very knowledgable about the German culture, which is a definite bonus.
Frau Euchner is a wonderful person who manages to combine professionalism with personality while maintaining an unparalleled classroom environment.
